The paper focuses on the security of machine learning models in mobile apps, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves analyzing the effectiveness of existing model protection techniques, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). The apps analyzed in the study include those related to face recognition and image recognition, which are subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential financial impact of stolen models, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
